The paper deals with the analysis of histopathology images using computational methods, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. The focus is on identifying cellular phenotypic differences between two molecularly distinct groups, which involves data analysis and clustering (cs.CR) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the potential application of the proposed framework to a wide range of biomedical research, which suggests a possible connection to neural engineering (cs.NE).
